        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2011-06-30 14:59:23.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me, approved\n\nThanks. This one is fine with me.\n\nA test checking that the original reproduce works well (i.e. write+truncate+write works well) would be welcomed. However, we need to fill the OST so i think it is better to wait until fallocate is supported by lustre (otherwise, filling an OST can take ages).\nWe also need to land this patch to b1_8 since some customers (e.g. DDN) enable async journal commit on b1_8.\n\nI'm going to port this patch to the orion branch. Thanks again.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
